## 6. FAQ

Q: Are all the required AI tools and extensions free for interns?
A: Yes. Core AI tools listed (ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, Copilot, Codeium, NotebookLM, Brave Leo, Fireflies, Loom) are free to use or provided by LightSpeed.

Q: How do I select which AI plugin to use for code?
A: Try Claude, Copilot, Gemini, Codeium, or CodeRabbit. Most interns install multiple and select based on workflow.

Q: Can I use AI for design work?
A: Yes — use Figma MCP, plugins, and built-in AI for mapping tokens, summarizing components, and generating starter code.

Q: Is my data/chat with these AI assistants private?
A: Policies vary. Tools like Brave Leo state they do not retain data. Always avoid submitting confidential info.

Q: Should I install AI Chrome extensions and mobile apps?
A: Yes — ChatGPT, Claude, Fireflies, Loom, etc. have Chrome extensions and mobile apps.

Q: Does this list change during the internship?
A: Yes — mentors will advise updates when agency recommendations change.

This guide aligns with the WordPress Internship and ensures interns have direct access and context for all AI tools used in study, code, and design workflows at LightSpeed.
